month.description: The month to show in the calendar.
month.name: month

numberOfMonths.description:
The number of months to show in the date picker. See also `pagedNavigation`
and `reverseMonths`.
numberOfMonths.name: numberOfMonths

fromMonth.description:
Allow navigation only after this month.

See also `toMonth`.
fromMonth.name: fromMonth

toMonth.description:
Allow navigation only before this month.

See also `fromMonth`.
toMonth.name: toMonth

pagedNavigation.description:
When displaying multiple months, the navigation will be paginated
displaying the `numberOfMonths` months at time instead of one.
pagedNavigation.name: pagedNavigation

reverseMonths.description:
Render the months in reversed order. Useful when `numberOfMonths` is
greater than 1, to display the most recent month first.
reverseMonths.name: reverseMonths

fixedWeeks.description:
Display 6 weeks per months, regardless the monthâ€™s number of weeks. Outside
days will be always shown if setting this to `true`. See also
`showOutsideDays`.
fixedWeeks.name: fixedWeeks

showCaption.description: Show the month caption displaying the month and the year.
showCaption.name: showCaption

showHead.description: Show the month head containing the weekday names.
showHead.name: showHead

showOutsideDays.description:
Show the outside days. An outside day is a day displayed in a month but
falling in the next or the previous month. See also
`enableOutsideDaysClick`.
showOutsideDays.name: showOutsideDays

enableOutsideDaysClick.description: Enable click event for outside days. See also `showOutsideDays`.
enableOutsideDaysClick.name: enableOutsideDaysClick

showWeekNumber.description: Show the week numbers. See also `onWeekNumberClick`.
showWeekNumber.name: showWeekNumber

showNavigation.description: Show the navigation bar. `onMonthChange` must be set.
showNavigation.name: showNavigation

startDay.description: The date passed when clicking the start button in the navigation.
startDay.name: startDay

startLabel.description:
Label used for the start button in Navigation. Set it to empty string to
hide the button.
startLabel.name: startLabel

prevLabel.description:
Label used for the previous month button in Navigation. Set it to empty
string to hide the button.
prevLabel.name: prevLabel

nextLabel.description:
Label used for the next month button in Navigation. Set it to empty string
to hide the button.
nextLabel.name: nextLabel

selected.description: Days that should appear as selected.
selected.name: selected

disabled.description: Days that should appear as disabled.
disabled.name: disabled

hidden.description: Days that should not appear in the calendar.
hidden.name: hidden

formatCaption.description:
Format the month caption text.

The formatter receives the month (as `Date` object) as first argument, and
an option object with `locale` as second argument. It must return a String.

The default format is "Month Year".
formatCaption.name: formatCaption

formatDay.description:
Format the content of the day element.

The formatter receives the day (as `Date` object) as first argument, and an option
object with `locale` as second argument. It must return a String.

Default is the day's date.
formatDay.name: formatDay

formatWeekdayName.description:
Format the weekday's name in the head element.

The formatter receives the day (as `Date` object) as first argument, and an option
object with `locale` as second argument. It must return a String.
formatWeekdayName.name: formatWeekdayName

formatWeekNumber.description:
Format the week numbers (when `showWeekNumber` is set).

The formatter receives the week number as first argument, and an option
object with `locale` as second argument. It must return a String.
formatWeekNumber.name: formatWeekNumber

components.description:
React components replacing the native ones.

TODO?: better description
components.name: components

onDayClick.description:
Event handler when the user clicks on a day. Receives a `DateWithModifiers`
object as first argument, and the native event as second argument.
onDayClick.name: onDayClick

onMonthChange.description:
Event handler when the month changes, e.g. when using the next/prev
navigation buttons. Receives a `Date` object as first argument, and the
native event as second argument.
onMonthChange.name: onMonthChange

onNextClick.description:
Event handler when the next navigation button is clicked. Receives a `Date`
object as first argument, and the native event as second argument.
onNextClick.name: onNextClick

onPrevClick.description:
Event handler when the prev navigation button is clicked. Receives a `Date`
object as first argument, and the native event as second argument.
onPrevClick.name: onPrevClick

onStartClick.description:
Event handler when the prev navigation button is clicked. Receives a `Date`
object as first argument, and the native event as second argument.
onStartClick.name: onStartClick
